  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\nNomachine remote admin software seems to break Prysm\r\n\r\nI followed [THIS](https://someresat.medium.com/guide-to-staking-on-ethereum-2-0-ubuntu-prysm-56f681646f74) guide to setup an ETH validator and everything worked fine until I installed Nomachine remote administrator program.\r\nThen Prysm started restarting in a loop:\r\n```\r\nDec 15 22:21:54 Staker validator[48358]: time=\"2020-12-15 22:21:54\" level=fatal msg=\"Could not determine if beacon chain started: could not setup beacon chain ChainStart streaming client: rpc error: code = Unavailable desc = connection closed\" prefix=validator\r\nDec 15 22:21:54 Staker systemd[1]: prysmvalidator.service: Main process exited, code=exited, status=1/FAILURE\r\nDec 15 22:21:54 Staker systemd[1]: prysmvalidator.service: Failed with result 'exit-code'.\r\nDec 15 22:21:59 Staker systemd[1]: prysmvalidator.service: Scheduled restart job, restart counter is at 495.\r\nDec 15 22:21:59 Staker systemd[1]: Stopped Prysm Eth2 Validator Client.\r\nDec 15 22:21:59 Staker systemd[1]: Started Prysm Eth2 Validator Client.\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen I uninstalled Nomachine and it started working again.\r\n\r\nDo you have an explanation why Nomachine might be breaking Prysm?\r\n\r\nUbuntu 20.04.1 LTS\r\n32GB RAM\r\n",
